## ğŸ¯ Overview

Welcome to the future of Kubernetes automation! ğŸŒŸ This MCP server brings the power of K8s to your AI assistant through clean, atomic tools. No more wrestling with YAML or memorizing kubectl commands - just pure, retro-cool automation! 

*Think of it as your AI's personal kubectl sidekick* ğŸ¤–âœ¨

## âœ¨ Features

### ğŸ® Core Kubernetes Operations
- **ğŸš¢ Pod Management**: List, create, delete, and get logs from pods
- **ğŸ  Namespace Operations**: List and switch between namespaces  
- **ğŸš€ Deployment Management**: Create, scale, and delete deployments
- **ğŸ—‘ï¸ Resource Operations**: Delete various Kubernetes resources
- **ğŸ”Œ Port Forwarding**: Forward local ports to pod ports
- **ğŸ“œ Logs Access**: Retrieve logs from specific pods and containers

### ğŸ—ï¸ MCP Architecture
- **âš›ï¸ Atomic Tools**: Each tool does one specific thing well
- **ğŸ¯ Clean APIs**: Well-defined input/output schemas for each operation
- **ğŸ›¡ï¸ Error Handling**: Structured error responses with actionable messages
- **ğŸ“¡ Transport Support**: stdio and SSE transport protocols

## ğŸ› ï¸ Available Tools

### ğŸ“‹ Core Kubernetes Operations
| Tool | Description | Parameters |
|------|-------------|------------|
| `get_pods` ğŸš¢ | List pods in a namespace | `namespace` (optional) |
| `get_namespaces` ğŸ  | List all namespaces | None |
| `create_deployment` ğŸš€ | Create a new deployment | `name`, `image`, `replicas`, `namespace` (optional) |
| `delete_resource` ğŸ—‘ï¸ | Delete a Kubernetes resource | `resource_type`, `name`, `namespace` (optional) |
| `get_logs` ğŸ“œ | Get logs from a pod | `pod_name`, `namespace` (optional), `container` (optional), `tail` (optional) |
| `port_forward` ğŸ”Œ | Forward local port to pod | `pod_name`, `local_port`, `pod_port`, `namespace` (optional) |
| `scale_deployment` ğŸ“ˆ | Scale a deployment | `name`, `replicas`, `namespace` (optional) |

### ğŸ“Š Advanced Operations  
| Tool | Description | Parameters |
|------|-------------|------------|
| `list_services` ğŸŒ | List services with detailed info | `namespace` (default: "default"), `label_selector` (optional) |
| `list_deployments` ğŸš€ | List deployments with replica status | `namespace` (default: "default"), `label_selector` (optional) |
| `list_nodes` ğŸ–¥ï¸ | List cluster nodes with status | `label_selector` (optional) |
| `describe_pod` ğŸ” | Get comprehensive pod details | `pod_name`, `namespace` (default: "default") |

### âš™ï¸ Cluster Management
| Tool | Description | Parameters |
|------|-------------|------------|
| `get_contexts` ğŸ”„ | List available kubectl contexts | None |
| `switch_context` ğŸ”€ | Switch to different context | `context_name` |

### ğŸ”§ Configuration Management
| Tool | Description | Parameters |
|------|-------------|------------|
| `create_config_map` ğŸ“ | Create a ConfigMap | `name`, `data` (dict), `namespace` (default: "default") |
| `create_secret` ğŸ” | Create a Secret | `name`, `data` (dict), `secret_type` (default: "Opaque"), `namespace` (default: "default") |

### ğŸ› ï¸ Troubleshooting
| Tool | Description | Parameters |
|------|-------------|------------|
| `explain_error` â“ | Explain K8s errors in plain English | `error_msg` |

